Students are expected to acquire knowledge in the following areas:

* To demonstrate a working knowledge of nanoscience & nanotechnology principles and applications;
* To explain the nanoscale paradigm in terms of properties and functions at the nanoscale dimension;
* To apply key concepts in materials science, chemistry, physics, biology, and engineering to the field of nanotechnology;
* To identify current nanotechnology solutions in design, engineering, and manufacturing, and where the field may evolve over the next 10 to 15 years.

